## 2. Tool/Function Registration

### AITool - Abstraction Layer

```csharp
public abstract class AITool
{
    public abstract string Name { get; }
    public abstract string? Description { get; }
    public abstract IReadOnlyDictionary<string, object> AdditionalProperties { get; }

    public object? GetService(Type serviceType, object? serviceKey = null)
    public T? GetService<T>(object? serviceKey = null) where T : class
}
```

**Pre-built AITool Implementations:**
- `HostedCodeInterpreterTool` - Allows AI to execute code
- `HostedWebSearchTool` - Web search capability
- `HostedVectorStoreContent` - Vector store access
- `HostedMcpServerTool` - MCP server integration

---

### AIFunction - Function Wrapper

```csharp
public abstract class AIFunction : AIFunctionDeclaration
{
    // Core invocation
    public async Task<object?> InvokeAsync(
        AIFunctionArguments arguments,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
    )

    protected abstract Task<object?> InvokeCoreAsync(
        AIFunctionArguments arguments,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken
    )

    // Metadata
    public virtual MethodInfo? UnderlyingMethod { get; }
    public abstract JsonSerializerOptions JsonSerializerOptions { get; }

    // Convert to declaration-only (non-invokable)
    public AIFunctionDeclaration AsDeclarationOnly()
}
```

---

### AIFunctionFactory - Creating Functions

Factory methods for creating `AIFunction` instances from .NET methods.

```csharp
public static class AIFunctionFactory
{
    // Create from delegate with options
    public static AIFunction Create(
        Delegate method,
        AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null
    )

    // Create with custom name/description
    public static AIFunction Create(
        Delegate method,
        string? name = null,
        string? description = null,
        JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null
    )
}

public class AIFunctionFactoryOptions
{
    // Serialization
    public JsonSerializerOptions? SerializerOptions { get; set; }

    // JSON Schema generation
    public AIJsonSchemaCreateOptions? JsonSchemaCreateOptions { get; set; }

    // Custom result marshaling
    public Func<object?, JsonSerializerOptions, object?>? MarshalResult { get; set; }

    // Exclude result schema from function declaration
    public bool ExcludeResultSchema { get; set; }

    // Custom parameter binding configuration
    public Action<AIFunctionDeclaration>? ConfigureParameterBinding { get; set; }
}
```

**Special Parameter Handling:**
- `CancellationToken` → Bound to invocation's cancellation token (excluded from schema)
- `IServiceProvider` → Bound from `AIFunctionArguments.Services` (excluded from schema)
- `AIFunctionArguments` → Bound directly (excluded from schema)
- All other parameters → Included in JSON schema, sourced from arguments dictionary

---

### AIFunctionArguments - Function Parameters

```csharp
public class AIFunctionArguments : IDictionary<string, object>
{
    // Constructors
    public AIFunctionArguments()
    public AIFunctionArguments(IDictionary<string, object>? arguments)
    public AIFunctionArguments(
        IDictionary<string, object>? arguments,
        IEqualityComparer<string> comparer
    )

    // Core dictionary interface (IDictionary<string, object>)
    public object this[string key] { get; set; }
    public ICollection<string> Keys { get; }
    public ICollection<object> Values { get; }
    public int Count { get; }
    public bool IsReadOnly { get; }

    public void Add(string key, object value)
    public bool TryGetValue(string key, out object? value)
    public bool Remove(string key)
    public void Clear()

    // Additional context (loosely-typed extra data)
    public IReadOnlyDictionary<string, object>? Context { get; set; }

    // Dependency injection
    public IServiceProvider? Services { get; set; }
}
```

---

### Registering Tools with Agent

Tools can be registered in multiple ways:

```csharp
// 1. Constructor parameter
var tools = new List<AITool>
{
    AIFunctionFactory.Create(MyMethod),
    new HostedCodeInterpreterTool(),
};
var agent = new ChatClientAgent(
    chatClient,
    tools: tools
);

// 2. ChatOptions during invocation
var options = new ChatClientAgentRunOptions
{
    ChatOptions = new ChatOptions
    {
        Tools = new[] { tool1, tool2 },
        ToolMode = ChatToolMode.Auto()
    }
};
await agent.RunAsync("Query", options: options);

// 3. ChatClientAgentOptions
var agentOptions = new ChatClientAgentOptions
{
    ChatOptions = new ChatOptions
    {
        Tools = tools
    }
};
```

